				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Bard role on Xegony<a name="57107"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 17 04 11:55 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Heya all,
<br />

<br />
There's a bit of discussion going on [in my guild] about strats for Xegony, and one thing I'm wondering is what role our rather limited number of bards (typically, just one or two) should play in this.
<br />

<br />
Possible options could be:
<br />

<br />
1) MT bard (PoV + Niv's for AC, Cha for DI) 
<br />
2) Cleric bard - They'll need all the mana they can get, so sit near clerics to play AE mana
<br />
3) Adds/DPS - Help the add teams by helping with CC/Kiting and boosting dps with muse.
<br />

<br />
If we can only fill one or two of these roles though, which are the most important and why? I tend to feel clerics first, then MT. However, there are disadvantages with pairing a bard with the MT, as they will suck up more mana for healing from the AE.
<br />

<br />
Any thoughts or suggestions? Or other roles bards should consider? Generally I get the impression the guild doesn't value the Charisma or AC on the MT much, but I feel it can really make a difference.. am I wrong in this?
<br />

<br />
PS: Trying not to get into the realm of giving out or getting detailed stats, just a high level discussion on roles<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
