				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard role on Xegony<a name="57124"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 17 04 12:45 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I think you are contributing more than your guild figures -- I think that if you have a singing booster like VOTS or Shadowsong Cloak, your contribution in terms of AC and DI odds is worth a lot.  Is it worth more than mana for the clerics?  That's harder to know.  If your clerics are running out of mana or close to it without a bard, then by all means, make that #1 priority.  I prefer to always have a main tank bard for those buffs you list when I direct raids.  But if it is a long fight, like Xegony, and clerics are struggling to keep up, that becomes the top priority.</span></td>
